headline: France's demographics debate focuses on birth rates while ignoring touchier measures
description: Politicians have struggled to address the various aspects of France's current demographic shift. The debate on the issue remains focused on boosting birth rates, while steering clear of more sensitive topics such as immigration or the retirement age.

headline: Epstein affair: The downfall of Peter Mandelson, the evil genius of the British Labour Party
French court to rule on July 7 in Marine Le Pen appeal trial
'Several dozen victims' and 14 arrests in suspected French-Senegalese pedophilia ring
description: Pierre Robert, a 73-year-old businessman from western France, was arrested in April 2025 and charged with human trafficking, aggravated pimping and rape of a minor under the age of 15. On Sunday, in coordination with French investigators, the Senegalese police announced the arrest of those they consider to be his local accomplices.

headline: Iran's reformist camp hit by wave of arrests
description: Several prominent members of the Reformist Front were detained in early February after the publication of a statement condemning the crackdown on protests. This latest offensive against a now-marginalized political faction is the most significant since 2009.

headline: 2026 Winter Olympics: Milan becomes a city-sized theme park
description: The northern Italian city, renowned for its cultural wealth, has been abuzz with the excitement of the Olympics since February 6. On the streets, visitors seem far more drawn to the fever of the Games than to Milan's traditional landmarks.

headline: 'The decline in birth rates is a social phenomenon, not a woman's responsibility'
description: Instead of questioning the collective factors behind declining birth rates, the dominant narrative shifts responsibility onto women, laments Brigitte Grésy, former president of France's High Council for Gender Equality, and Micheline Misrahi-Abadou, professor at the faculty of medicine of Paris-Saclay University.

description: The emblematic minister from President François Mitterrand's era was forced to step down as president of the Arab World Institute in Paris. Former allies and rivals have begun to speak out about a man who used his influence and network to maintain a lavish lifestyle.

headline: Emmanuel Macron: 'Now is the time for the EU to launch a joint borrowing capacity, through eurobonds'
description: Two days ahead of a meeting of European Union heads of state and government in Brussels, the French president calls on the 27 member states, in an interview with Le Monde and several other European newspapers, to make joint investments in protecting the environment, as well as in artificial intelligence and quantum technology, to avoid falling behind.

headline: France's municipal elections at risk of foreign interference
description: Structurally less attractive to foreign spies than legislative elections, municipal elections are not immune to deception, most of which tends to be local.
